# Launch Model Definitions for Modules and External Services (Stage 1 Contract)

## Purpose

This document defines **how anything in the platform is launched**.

It ensures: - no random links - no frontend-invented behavior -
consistent module execution - controlled integration of external systems

If this document is ignored, the platform becomes a pile of buttons that
open unpredictable things.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 1. Core Concept

Every launchable item is a **governed object**, not a link.

A launchable object must always define: - object_type - key -
availability - launch_method - launch_target - reason_codes (if
blocked) - remediation (if blocked)

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 2. Launchable Object Types

  Type                Description
  ------------------- ---------------------------------------------------
  platform_module     Core platform capability (Sales, Customers, etc.)
  external_service    Third-party or repo-based system
  admin_tool          Internal operational tools
  reporting_surface   Dashboards / analytics
  document_service    DocuShare / file-based services
  learning_surface    LMS / knowledge systems

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 3. Launch Methods

Every object must define ONE method:

  Method     Behaviour
  ---------- ----------------------------------
  native     Render inside platform
  embed      Load inside controlled iframe
  sso        Backend generates secure session
  redirect   Controlled external redirect
  none       Not launchable

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 4. Availability States

  State                 Meaning
  --------------------- -------------------------
  available             Launch allowed
  restricted            No entitlement
  pending               Awaiting activation
  onboarding_required   Setup incomplete
  billing_hold          Payment issue
  compliance_hold       Compliance block
  inactive              Disabled
  maintenance           Temporarily unavailable

Frontend must NEVER infer these.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 5. Standard Launch Model

``` json
{
  "object_type": "platform_module",
  "key": "sales",
  "availability": "available",
  "launch": {
    "method": "native",
    "route": "/app/modules/sales",
    "target_url": null
  },
  "reason_codes": [],
  "remediation": null
}
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 6. Blocked Launch Example

``` json
{
  "object_type": "platform_module",
  "key": "finance",
  "availability": "restricted",
  "launch": {
    "method": "none"
  },
  "reason_codes": ["ENTITLEMENT_MISSING"],
  "remediation": {
    "type": "upgrade_plan",
    "route": "/portal/membership"
  }
}
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 7. Launch Execution Flow

## Step 1: User clicks module

Frontend calls: GET /launch/readiness/{type}/{key}

## Step 2: Backend responds

-   availability
-   launch method
-   reason codes
-   remediation

## Step 3: If allowed

POST /launch/execute

## Step 4: Backend returns execution

``` json
{
  "execution": {
    "method": "sso",
    "target_url": "https://secure-launch"
  }
}
```

Frontend acts. Nothing more.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 8. Reason Codes

  Code                    Meaning
  ----------------------- ----------------------
  ENTITLEMENT_MISSING     Not included in plan
  BILLING_HOLD            Payment issue
  ONBOARDING_INCOMPLETE   Setup required
  ROLE_NOT_ALLOWED        Permission issue
  MAINTENANCE             System unavailable

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 9. Remediation Types

  Type                  Action
  --------------------- ------------------
  upgrade_plan          Go to membership
  resolve_billing       Go to billing
  continue_onboarding   Resume setup
  contact_support       Open support
  none                  No action

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 10. Admin Launch Configuration

Admins must control:

``` json
{
  "visibility": {
    "client": true,
    "admin": true
  },
  "launch": {
    "method": "sso"
  },
  "requirements": {
    "requires_entitlement": true,
    "requires_onboarding": true
  }
}
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 11. Surface Rules

## Public

-   Can view
-   Cannot launch privileged systems

## Client

-   Launch based on entitlement + state

## Admin

-   Full operational access (role dependent)

## App Layer

-   Central launch control

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 12. Hard Rules

Frontend must NOT: - construct URLs - decide access - bypass launch
API - embed systems directly

Backend must: - return full launch model - enforce all rules

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Definition of Done

-   Every module has a launch model
-   Every external service has a launch model
-   No raw links exist in UI
-   All launches pass through API
-   Blocked states are explainable
